[normal]David Behan[bold]: 
[normal]If you look at the history of Southern Cross, what began to happen was they were not able to pay back 
[normal]on 
[normal]this complicated loan structure and operating structure that they had. Quality was falling because they could not pay that back so they started skimping on support staff, training and managerial staff. Quality fell even further. 
[normal]There
[normal] was effectively a race to the bottom as the revenues could not 
[normal]pay 
[normal]back and the quality was suffering. 
[normal]The
[normal] relationship between quality and finance was quite apparent in Southern Cross. 
